I think the latest attempt to `Build #227 (Jul 3, 2017 2:25:07 AM) ` failed for `Windows GPU.` 

I believe the most recent and stable version built was `tensorflow_gpu-1.2.0-cp36-cp36m-win_amd64.whl`.

However, the `pip install --upgrade tensorflow_gpu ` is attempting to download the `tensorflow_gpu-1.2.1-cp36-cp36m-win_amd64.whl` which is not the `build : pass` so it's not working I guess.

Hope it answers your question. Also, no one can temper hashes :)
